OL,3,CNow we expect answers, says son of
OL,4,Csoldier killed in 1994 Chinook crash
OL,6,FThe bereaved families on Monday
OL,7,Fpublished 225 new questions about the
OL,8,Fcircumstances leading up to the crash,
OL,9,Fincluding how and why the
OL,10,F"unairworthy" aircraft was chosen for
OL,11,Fthe journey and why "key technical
OL,12,Fdocuments" were withheld from multiple
OL,13,Finquiries.
OL,15,FThey come on top of 110 questions that
OL,16,Fwere published previously, meaning the
OL,17,Ffamilies are now seeking answers to a
OL,18,Ftotal of 335 questions about the crash.
